== Pickled Red Onion ==

Wash and dry produce. Halve, peel, and very thinly slice @red onion{1}. In a
#small bowl{}, combine half the @red wine vinegar{5%teaspoon} (you'll use the
rest later), ½ tsp sugar (1 tsp for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{pinch}
and @pepper{pinch}. Add ¼ of the sliced onion; toss to coat. Set aside,
stirring occasionally, until ready to serve.

== Cabbage Slaw ==

In a #medium bowl{}, combine @sour cream{2%tablespoon}, remaining vinegar,
½ tsp sugar (1 tsp for 4 servings), and @sriracha{1%teaspoon} (start with half
and add more if you like things spicy). Stir in @shredded red cabbage{4%ounce}.
Season with salt and pepper. Set aside, stirring occasionally, until ready to
serve.

== Chicken and Assembly ==

Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over
medium-high heat. Add remaining onion and cabbage and season with salt and
pepper. Cook, stirring, until slightly softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pat @chicken breast strips{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}.
Add to pan with veggies along with another drizzle of oil, salt, and pepper.
Cook, stirring often, until chicken is browned and cooked through,
~{4-6%minutes}.

Add @teriyaki sauce{8%tablespoon} to pan; bring to a boil. Reduce to a low
simmer and cook until sauce is slightly thickened and coats chicken and
veggies, ~{4-6%minutes}. Stir in half the @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon}. Season
with salt and pepper.

Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp paper towels and microwave until warm and
pliable, ~{30%seconds}. Divide chicken and veggie mixture (using a
#slotted spoon{} if needed) between tortillas. Top with cabbage slaw and
pickled onion. Sprinkle with remaining sesame seeds and serve.

> One bite will make your taste buds sing.